{
  "text": "Scaffolds based on a biocompatible and biodegradable elastomer elastomeric poly (glycerol sebacate) (PGS) have recently been developed that offer desirable mechanical properties such as of low tissue-like stiffness and rubber-like elasticity, thereby allowing for large deformations. [CITATION_1] 13 Coating of surfaces with cell-adhesion mediators like fibronectin (FN), laminin (LM), or other ECM components enhances cell attachment, proliferation, differentiation, and migration. 14 In an attempt to differentiate the mechanochemical characteristics of scaffold materials and understand the cell-surface interactions, we precoated the PGS scaffold with ECM proteins and assessed the cellular behavior of the EPC.",
